Washing Machine (1961), Roy Lichtenstein
Recently, Andrej Karpathy, head of AI at Tesla, wrote &ldquo;Software 2.0.&quot;, describing what he sees as a fundamental shift in the way software works. Software 1.0 is &ldquo;explicit instructions to the computer written by a programmer.&rdquo;
Instead of writing lines of code, he writes that, &ldquo;Software 2.0 is written in neural network weights.&rdquo;
 No human is involved in writing this code because there are a lot of weights (typical networks might have millions), and coding directly in weights is kind of hard (I tried).
